+{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01ExFGrJ6bM423idQq7yTWkD","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have all the information. Let me compile a comprehensive report for you.\n\n## Project Structure Report\n\n### Directory Tree\n```\n/workspace/\n├── .eslintrc.cjs\n├── .gitignore\n├── .git/\n├── .thunderdome/\n├── TASK.md\n├── package.json\n├── package-lock.json\n├── tsconfig.json\n├── vitest.config.ts\n├── phases/\n│   ├── phase-01.md\n│   ├── phase-02.md\n│   ├── phase-03.md\n│   ├── phase-04.md\n│   ├── phase-05.md\n│   ├── phase-06.md\n│   ├── phase-07.md\n│   ├── phase-08.md\n│   ├── phase-09.md\n│   ├── phase-10.md\n│   ├── phase-11.md\n│   └── phase-12.md\n└── src/\n    └── .gitkeep (empty directory)\n```\n\n### package.json\n```json\n{\n  \"name\": \"bench-task-queue\",\n  \"version\": \"1.0.0\",\n  \"description\": \"Task queue marathon benchmark\",\n  \"type\": \"module\",\n  \"scripts\": {\n    \"build\": \"tsc\",\n    \"lint\": \"eslint src/\",\n    \"test\": \"vitest run\"\n  },\n  \"devDependencies\": {\n    \"@types/node\": \"^25.2.3\",\n    \"@typescript-eslint/eslint-plugin\": \"^7.0.0\",\n    \"@typescript-eslint/parser\": \"^7.0.0\",\n    \"eslint\": \"^8.56.0\",\n    \"typescript\": \"^5.4.0\",\n    \"@vitest/coverage-v8\": \"^2.0.0\",\n    \"vitest\": \"^2.0.0\"\n  }\n}\n```\n\n### tsconfig.json\n```json\n{\n  \"compilerOptions\": {\n    \"target\": \"ES2022\",\n    \"module\": \"Node16\",\n    \"moduleResolution\": \"Node16\",\n    \"outDir\": \"./dist\",\n    \"rootDir\": \"./src\",\n    \"strict\": true,\n    \"esModuleInterop\": true,\n    \"skipLibCheck\": true,\n    \"forceConsistentCasingInFileNames\": true,\n    \"resolveJsonModule\": true,\n    \"declaration\": true,\n    \"declarationMap\": true,\n    \"sourceMap\": true\n  },\n  \"include\": [\"src/**/*\"],\n  \"exclude\": [\"node_modules\", \"dist\", \"tests\"]\n}\n```\n\n### vitest.config.ts\n```typescript\nimport { defineConfig } from 'vitest/config';\n\nexport default defineConfig({\n  test: {\n    globals: true,\n    testTimeout: 10000,\n  },\n});\n```\n\n### .eslintrc.cjs\n```javascript\nmodule.exports = {\n  parser: '@typescript-eslint/parser',\n  plugins: ['@typescript-eslint'],\n  extends: ['eslint:recommended', 'plugin:@typescript-eslint/recommended'],\n  parserOptions: {\n    ecmaVersion: 2022,\n    sourceType: 'module',\n  },\n  rules: {\n    '@typescript-eslint/no-unused-vars': ['error', { argsIgnorePattern: '^_', varsIgnorePattern: '^_' }],\n  },\n  env: {\n    node: true,\n    es2022: true,\n  },\n};\n```\n\n### .gitignore\n```\nnode_modules/\ndist/\n*.tsbuildinfo\n```\n\n### TASK.md\n**Summary:** Build a fully-featured in-memory task queue system through 12 progressive phases, similar to Bull, BeeQueue, or Celery.\n\nKey points:\n- Export main API from `src/index.ts`\n- All implementation under `src/`\n- No external runtime dependencies\n- Must pass `npm run build`, `npm run lint`, and `npm run test`\n\nThe 12 phases:\n1. Basic FIFO queue\n2. Named queues\n3. Priority support\n4. Delayed and scheduled tasks\n5. Retry with backoff\n6. Dead letter queue\n7. Task dependencies\n8. Concurrency control\n9. Progress tracking and cancellation\n10. Recurring tasks\n11. Middleware pipeline\n12. Graceful shutdown\n\n---\n\n## Phase Files (All 12)\n\n### Phase 1: Basic FIFO Queue\n- Queue accepts payload, returns task object\n- Each task: unique ID (UUID), status, creation timestamp\n- New tasks start \"pending\"\n- Retrieving next task returns oldest pending task, transitions to \"processing\"\n- No tasks available returns `null`\n- Track how many tasks are waiting\n\n### Phase 2: Named Queues\n- Tasks added to specific named queue (default if no name given)\n- Each named queue operates independently\n- Implicit queue creation on first task\n- List all queue names\n- Non-existent/empty queue returns `null`\n- Backward-compatible with Phase 1\n\n### Phase 3: Priority\n- Priority levels 1 (highest) to 10 (lowest), default 5\n- Higher-priority tasks returned first\n- Same priority = FIFO order\n- Invalid priority (outside 1-10) = error\n- Per-queue priority ordering\n- Task exposes its priority\n\n### Phase 4: Delayed and Scheduled Tasks\n- Tasks can have delay (milliseconds) or specific future time\n- Delayed tasks added immediately but not retrieved until available\n- Non-delayed preferred over unavailable delayed tasks\n- Multiple simultaneous delays ordered by: availability time → priority → FIFO\n- Task indicates availability time\n- Works with named queues\n\n### Phase 5: Retry with Backoff\n- Mark processing task as completed or failed\n- Failed tasks with retries re-added with delay\n- Exponential backoff: `baseDelay * 2^(attempt - 1)` (1s, 2s, 4s...)\n- Default max retries: 3 (configurable)\n- Base delay default: 1000ms (configurable)\n- Track attempt count\n- Retried tasks keep original queue and priority\n- Exhausted retries = failed state\n\n### Phase 6: Dead Letter Queue\n- Tasks exhausting retries moved to DLQ for their original queue\n- View all dead-lettered tasks for queue\n- Retain error info and failure count\n- Move dead-lettered task back to original queue\n- Clear all DLQ tasks for queue\n- Each queue has independent DLQ\n\n### Phase 7: Task Dependencies\n- Tasks can specify task IDs that must complete first\n- Blocked tasks not returned when retrieving\n- When dependency completes, check if blocked tasks unblock\n- Detect and reject circular dependencies at creation\n- Non-existent task dependency = error\n- Failed dependency doesn't auto-fail dependents\n- Inspect task's dependency status\n\n### Phase 8: Concurrency Control\n- Each queue has max concurrency setting (limiting simultaneous processing)\n- Concurrency limit reached = return `null` even if pending tasks exist\n- Completing/failing task frees slot\n- Default: no limit (unlimited)\n- Set and query concurrency limit and current active count\n- Highest-priority available task chosen subject to concurrency limit\n\n### Phase 9: Progress Tracking and Cancellation\n- Processing task reports progress (0-100%) with optional message\n- Query task's current progress\n- Subscribe to progress updates, receive notifications\n- Subscriptions cancellable\n- Pending/processing tasks can be cancelled\n- Cancelled pending tasks removed from queue\n- Cancelled processing tasks status updated\n- Cancelled tasks never retried\n\n### Phase 10: Recurring Tasks\n- Schedule associates cron expression, queue, and task template\n- Simple cron subset:\n  - `*/N * * * *` -- every N minutes\n  - `0 * * * *` -- every hour on the hour\n  - `0 0 * * *` -- every day at midnight\n- Create, remove, list schedules\n- Manual \"tick\"/\"check\" to evaluate schedules and enqueue due tasks (for testing)\n- Enqueued recurring tasks = regular tasks\n- Removing schedule stops future occurrences\n\n### Phase 11: Middleware Pipeline\n- Middleware registered per queue\n- Task passes through all middleware in order before handler\n- Middleware receives task and \"next\" function\n- Not calling \"next\" skips task processing\n- Middleware can modify task\n- Middleware error = task marked failed\n- Processing function/handler registered per queue, invoked after middleware\n- Each queue has independent middleware stack\n\n### Phase 12: Graceful Shutdown\n- Shutdown signals stop accepting new tasks\n- New tasks after shutdown = error\n- Wait for processing tasks, configurable timeout\n- Force-cancel if not complete within timeout\n- Register callbacks for shutdown process\n- Produce summary: tasks completed, force-cancelled, duration\n- Multiple shutdowns safe, return same result\n- No processing tasks = complete immediately\n\n---\n\n## src/ Directory\nCurrently empty (contains only `.gitkeep`)\n\n---\n\n## Summary\nThis is a **greenfield project** for building a sophisticated in-memory task queue system incrementally through 12 phases. The project has:\n- All necessary dev dependencies (TypeScript, ESLint, Vitest)\n- Proper TypeScript configuration with ES2022 target and strict mode\n- Empty `src/` directory ready for implementation\n- Comprehensive phase requirements in the `phases/` directory\n- No external runtime dependencies allowed"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: abe75b2 (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 20671\ntool_uses: 23\nduration_ms: 35600</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"506dd83c-382a-45ba-8c08-6cb3db03e95b","uuid":"62fa6353-2821-47bd-b20b-6bafeb1278f6","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Explore the entire project structure. I need:\n1. The full directory tree\n2. Contents of all files in phases/ directory (all .md files)\n3. Contents of package.json, tsconfig.json, and any config files\n4. Contents of any existing files in src/\n5. Contents of TASK.md if it exists\n\nBe very thorough - read every phase file and every config file.","agentId":"abe75b2","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have all the information. Let me compile a comprehensive report for you.\n\n## Project Structure Report\n\n### Directory Tree\n```\n/workspace/\n├── .eslintrc.cjs\n├── .gitignore\n├── .git/\n├── .thunderdome/\n├── TASK.md\n├── package.json\n├── package-lock.json\n├── tsconfig.json\n├── vitest.config.ts\n├── phases/\n│   ├── phase-01.md\n│   ├── phase-02.md\n│   ├── phase-03.md\n│   ├── phase-04.md\n│   ├── phase-05.md\n│   ├── phase-06.md\n│   ├── phase-07.md\n│   ├── phase-08.md\n│   ├── phase-09.md\n│   ├── phase-10.md\n│   ├── phase-11.md\n│   └── phase-12.md\n└── src/\n    └── .gitkeep (empty directory)\n```\n\n### package.json\n```json\n{\n  \"name\": \"bench-task-queue\",\n  \"version\": \"1.0.0\",\n  \"description\": \"Task queue marathon benchmark\",\n  \"type\": \"module\",\n  \"scripts\": {\n    \"build\": \"tsc\",\n    \"lint\": \"eslint src/\",\n    \"test\": \"vitest run\"\n  },\n  \"devDependencies\": {\n    \"@types/node\"