asks for queue\n- Retain error info and failure count\n- Move dead-lettered task back to original queue\n- Clear all DLQ tasks for queue\n- Each queue has independent DLQ\n\n### Phase 7: Task Dependencies\n- Tasks can specify task IDs that must complete first\n- Blocked tasks not returned when retrieving\n- When dependency completes, check if blocked tasks unblock\n- Detect and reject circular dependencies at creation\n- Non-existent task dependency = error\n- Failed dependency doesn't auto-fail dependents\n- Inspect task's dependency status\n\n### Phase 8: Concurrency Control\n- Each queue has max concurrency setting (limiting simultaneous processing)\n- Concurrency limit reached = return `null` even if pending tasks exist\n- Completing/failing task frees slot\n- Default: no limit (unlimited)\n- Set and query concurrency limit and current active count\n- Highest-priority available task chosen subject to concurrency limit\n\n### Phase 9: Progress Tracking and Cancellation\n- Processing task reports progress (0-100%) with optional message\n- Query task's current progress\n- Subscribe to progress updates, receive notifications\n- Subscriptions cancellable\n- Pending/processing tasks can be cancelled\n- Cancelled pending tasks removed from queue\n- Cancelled processing tasks status updated\n- Cancelled tasks never retried\n\n### Phase 10: Recurring Tasks\n- Schedule associates cron expression, queue, and task template\n- Simple cron subset:\n  - `*/N * * * *` -- every N minutes\n  - `0 * * * *` -- every hour on the hour\n  - `0 0 * * *` -- every day at midnight\n- Create, remove, list schedules\n- Manual \"tick\"/\"check\" to evaluate schedules and enqueue due tasks (for testing)\n- Enqueued recurring tasks = regular tasks\n- Removing schedule stops future occurrences\n\n### Phase 11: Middleware Pipeline\n- Middleware registered per queue\n- Task passes through all middleware in order before handler\n- Middleware receives task and \"next\" function\n- Not calling \"next\" skips task processing\n- Middleware can modify task\n- Middleware error = task marked failed\n- Processing function/handler registered per queue, invoked after middleware\n- Each queue has independent middleware stack\n\n### Phase 12: Graceful Shutdown\n- Shutdown signals stop accepting new tasks\n- New tasks after shutdown = error\n- Wait for processing tasks, configurable timeout\n- Force-cancel if not complete within timeout\n- Register callbacks for shutdown process\n- Produce summary: tasks completed, force-cancelled, duration\n- Multiple shutdowns safe, return same result\n- No processing tasks = complete immediately\n\n---\n\n## src/ Directory\nCurrently empty (contains only `.gitkeep`)\n\n---\n\n## Summary\nThis is a **greenfield project** for building a sophisticated in-memory task queue system incrementally through 12 phases. The project has:\n- All necessary dev dependencies (TypeScript, ESLint, Vitest)\n- Proper TypeScript configuration with ES2022 target and strict mode\n- Empty `src/` directory ready for implementation\n- Comprehensive phase requirements in the `phases/` directory\n- No external runtime dependencies allowed"}],"totalDurationMs":35600,"totalTokens":20671,"totalToolUseCount":23,"usage":{"input_tokens":7,"cache_creation_input_tokens":527,"cache_read_input_tokens":17869,"output_tokens":2268,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":527,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[]}}}
